---

<Layout>
  <div class="container my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-10">
        <a href="/courses/foce/" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-light mb-3">
          <i class="si-arrow-left"></i> Back
        </a>

        <h1>Activity 1.11: If, Elif, and Else</h1>
        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-5" />

        <!-- Launch / Concept -->
        <section id="launch">
          <Presentation>
            <section>
              <h2>Activity 1.11</h2>
              <h3 class="text-sn-theme">If, Elif, and Else</h3>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Concepts</h2>
              <p>else</p>
              <p>elif</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>else</h2>
              <p>
                <b class="text-sn-theme">else</b> runs when the
                <code>if</code> condition was <code>False</code> &mdash;
                exactly one of the two blocks always runs.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure1} frame="code" lang="python" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>else</h2>
              <Code code={Figure2} frame="terminal" lang="txt" showLineNumbers={false} />
              <Code code={Figure3} frame="terminal" lang="txt" showLineNumbers={false} class="mt-2" />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>The Problem with Independent ifs</h2>
              <p>
                Last activity's Letter Grade Calculator needed a two-part
                condition for every range, like
                <code>grade &gt;= 80 and grade &lt; 90</code>. That gets
                repetitive fast.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>elif</h2>
              <p>
                <b class="text-sn-theme">elif</b> (short for "else if")
                chains conditions together &mdash; Python checks them in
                order and runs only the <b>first</b> one that's
                <code>True</code>.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure4} frame="code" lang="python" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>elif</h2>
              <Code code={Figure5} frame="terminal" lang="txt" showLineNumbers={false} />
              <Code code={Figure6} frame="terminal" lang="txt" showLineNumbers={false} class="mt-2" />
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Today's Objectives</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>Writing an <code>if</code>/<code>else</code> statement</li>
                <li>Chaining conditions with <code>elif</code></li>
                <li>Importing the <code>random</code> module</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Terms</h2>
              <div class="text-start">
                <dl>
                  <dt>else</dt>
                  <dd>Runs when every condition before it was <code>False</code>.</dd>
                  <dt>elif</dt>
                  <dd>Chains another condition onto an <code>if</code> &mdash; only the first true branch runs.</dd>
                  <dt>Module</dt>
                  <dd>A collection of tools not built directly into Python &mdash; you bring it in with <code>import</code>.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </section>
          </Presentation>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Build -->
        <section id="build">
          <h2>Build</h2>

          <p>
            Create a new Python script named <b class="text-sn-theme">1-11-if-elif-else.py</b>.
          </p>

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 1: Chinese Zodiac Calendar</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Use the birth year's remainder after dividing by 12 to determine a zodiac animal, with an <code>elif</code> chain.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task1} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-11-if-elif-else.py" mark="9-32" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 2: Lottery Game</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Import the <code>random</code> module to generate two winning numbers.</li>
            <li>Compare the player's two picks against them with <code>elif</code>.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task2} frame="code" lang="python" title="1-11-if-elif-else.py" mark="44-45,54-59" ins="36-59" />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Checkpoint -->
        <section id="checkpoint">
          <h2>Checkpoint</h2>

          <p>Verify your program works correctly.</p>

          <Code
            code={SampleOutput}
            frame="terminal"
            lang="txt"
            showLineNumbers={false}
            title="Example Output"
          />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Reflection -->
        <section id="reflection">
          <h2>Reflection</h2>

          <p>Answer the following questions before submitting your work.</p>

          <ol>
            <li>In an <code>if</code>/<code>elif</code>/<code>else</code> chain, how many of the blocks can run at most?</li>
            <li>Why didn't the Zodiac Calendar need a final <code>elif zodiac_number == 11:</code> check before its <code>else</code>?</li>
            <li>What is a module, and why did the Lottery Game need to <code>import random</code> when nothing before it needed an import?</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Submit -->
        <section id="submit">
          <h2>Submit</h2>

          <p>Submit the required files to the appropriate dropbox.</p>

          <h1
            class="text-center mt-5 text-sn-theme border border-primary slow-flash"
          >
            Activity Complete
          </h1>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
